Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.05,0:00:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Day 4, a 7-cent mismatch led me to a bug that was quietly eating 5 times my fees.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.71,0:00:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I can't code.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.12,0:00:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}AI trades my thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.26,0:00:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Day 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.42,0:00:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}End of day reconcile — bot's internal accounting said one thing, Coinbase said another.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.28,0:00:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}7 cents apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.10,0:00:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Honestly?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.17,0:00:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I almost let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.92,0:00:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Seven cents.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.47,0:00:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Who cares.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.79,0:00:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I checked anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.36,0:00:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And found — the fee formula was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.79,0:00:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Supposed to be notional times rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.39,0:00:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I'd written margin times rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.97,0:00:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Underreporting fees by 5x.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.83,0:00:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Every single trade.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.71,0:00:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}One trade — you'd never notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.61,0:00:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}A thousand trades — different business.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.57,0:00:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You know the worst kind of bug?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.61,0:00:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Not the one that crashes your program.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.19,0:00:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}That one gets fixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.90,0:00:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The worst one is the bug that lets you feel like you're winning on your way to losing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.53,0:01:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Most people don't go broke from one big mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.10,0:01:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}They go broke from a thousand quiet defaults that compound into a surprise that wasn't a surprise to anyone paying attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.96,0:01:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Day 5 tomorrow — an agent I built posted a message I never asked for.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.83,0:01:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Follow along.
